---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
    title="Men's Leadership Coaching: Developing Executive Presence | Tom Jameson"
    description="Build executive presence and leadership skills through targeted men's coaching that focuses on communication, decision-making, and team management."
    canonical="https://tomcoaching.com/blog/mens-leadership-coaching"
>
    <div class="blog-post-container">
        <div class="container">
            <nav class="breadcrumb">
                <a href="/">Home</a> / <a href="/blog">Blog</a> / Men's Leadership Coaching
            </nav>

            <article class="blog-post">
                <header class="post-header">
                    <div class="post-meta">
                        <span class="category">Leadership</span>
                        <span class="date">December 19, 2024</span>
                    </div>
                    <h1>Men's Leadership Coaching: Developing Executive Presence</h1>
                    <p class="post-excerpt">Build executive presence and leadership skills through targeted men's coaching that focuses on communication, decision-making, and team management.</p>
                </header>

                <div class="post-content">
                    <p>Men's leadership coaching focuses on developing the essential skills and presence needed to lead effectively in today's professional environment. Executive presence goes beyond technical competence, encompassing communication style, emotional intelligence, and the ability to inspire and motivate teams toward shared goals.</p>

                    <p>Professional leadership coaching helps men develop confidence in decision-making, improve their communication skills, and build the emotional intelligence necessary for effective team management. Coaches work with clients to identify their leadership style, address areas for improvement, and develop strategies for building trust and credibility with colleagues and team members.</p>

                    <p>Effective leadership coaching includes developing presentation skills, learning to give and receive feedback constructively, managing conflict resolution, and building strategic thinking capabilities. Coaches help clients understand how to balance assertiveness with empathy, create inclusive work environments, and develop the resilience needed to navigate complex organizational challenges.</p>

                    <p>Whether you're transitioning into a leadership role, looking to improve your management skills, or seeking to develop executive presence for career advancement, men's leadership coaching can provide the guidance and support you need to become a more effective and confident leader.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="related-articles">
                    <h3>Related Articles</h3>
                    <div class="related-grid">
                        <a href="/blog/mens-career-coaching" class="related-card">
                            <h4>Men's Career Coaching: Breaking Through Professional Barriers</h4>
                            <p>Learn how career coaching can help you advance professionally.</p>
                        </a>
                        <a href="/blog/mens-midlife-coaching" class="related-card">
                            <h4>Men's Midlife Coaching: Navigating Life Transitions</h4>
                            <p>Navigate midlife transitions with confidence.</p>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="post-cta">
                    <h3>Ready to Develop Your Leadership Skills?</h3>
                    <p>Take the first step towards becoming a more effective leader with professional coaching support.</p>
                    <a href="/#contact" class="btn">Book Your Consultation Today</a>
                </div>
            </article>
        </div>
    </div>

    <style>
        .blog-post-container {
            min-height: 100vh;
            background: white;
            padding: 80px 0;
        }

        .breadcrumb {
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            color: #666;
        }

        .breadcrumb a {
            color: #d0c39b;
            text-decoration: none;
        }

        .breadcrumb a:hover {
            color: #172a22;
        }

        .blog-post {
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            background: white;
            padding: 3rem;
            border-radius: 12px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        .post-header {
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .post-meta {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }

        .category {
            background: #d0c39b;
            color: #172a22;
            padding: 0.3rem 0.8rem;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-weight: 600;
        }

        .date {
            color: #666;
        }

        .post-header h1 {
            font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: #172a22;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            line-height: 1.2;
        }

        .post-excerpt {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: #666;
            font-style: italic;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .post-content {
            line-height: 1.8;
            color: #333;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
        }

        .post-content p {
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .related-articles {
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
            padding-top: 2rem;
            border-top: 1px solid #e9ecef;
        }

        .related-articles h3 {
            font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
            color: #172a22;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        .related-grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
            gap: 1.5rem;
        }

        .related-card {
            background: #f8f9fa;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 8px;
            text-decoration: none;
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
            border: 1px solid #e9ecef;
        }

        .related-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-3px);
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
        }

        .related-card h4 {
            color: #172a22;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
        }

        .related-card p {
            color: #666;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
            margin: 0;
        }

        .post-cta {
            text-align: center;
            background: linear-gradient(135deg, #172a22 0%, #1e3a2e 100%);
            color: #d0c39b;
            padding: 2.5rem;
            border-radius: 12px;
        }

        .post-cta h3 {
            font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
            font-size: 1.8rem;
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
        }

        .post-cta p {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            margin-bottom: 2rem;
            opacity: 0.9;
        }

        .btn {
            display: inline-block;
            background-color: #d0c39b;
            color: #172a22;
            padding: 15px 30px;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 8px;
            font-weight: 600;
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(208, 195, 155, 0.3);
        }

        .btn:hover {
            background-color: #c4b082;
            transform: translateY(-2px);
            box-shadow: 0 6px 20px rgba(208, 195, 155, 0.4);
        }

        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .blog-post {
                padding: 2rem;
                margin: 0 1rem;
            }
            
            .post-header h1 {
                font-size: 2rem;
            }
            
            .post-meta {
                flex-direction: column;
                gap: 0.5rem;
            }
        }
    </style>

